title Connected Customer Journey in Retail
style wardley

// Anchors — two user types: the retail customer and the producer supplying goods
anchor Customer [0.98, 0.55]
anchor Producer [0.95, 0.45]

// Layer 1 — user needs (directly user-facing, close to the anchors)
component Need to Acquire Goods [0.90, 0.78]
component Need to Sell Goods [0.88, 0.55]
component Goods and Services [0.82, 0.62]
component Retail Experience [0.80, 0.40]

// Layer 2 — channels the value flows through
component Physical Store [0.72, 0.82]
component E-Commerce Site [0.70, 0.72]
component Mobile App [0.68, 0.60]
component Telesales [0.66, 0.85]
component Social Commerce [0.64, 0.35]

// Layer 3 — experience layer (sensory, trust, engagement, discovery)
component Sensory Experience [0.58, 0.30]
component Virtual / AR Try-On [0.56, 0.20]
component Personalisation Engine [0.54, 0.40]
component Product Discovery [0.52, 0.48]
component Engagement and Loyalty [0.50, 0.55]
component Trust and Privacy [0.48, 0.50]
component Returns and Reverse Logistics [0.46, 0.65]
component Customer Support [0.44, 0.70]

// Layer 4 — data and behavioural inputs (demographics, societal behaviour, segmentation)
component Demographic Segmentation [0.38, 0.72]
component Societal Behaviour Signals [0.36, 0.28]
component Customer Data Platform [0.34, 0.55]
component Consent Management [0.32, 0.60]

// Layer 5 — commoditised infrastructure
component Payment Processing [0.26, 0.90]
component Identity / KYC [0.24, 0.78]
component Inventory and Fulfilment [0.22, 0.72]
component Logistics Network [0.20, 0.82]
component CRM [0.18, 0.80]
component Cloud Compute [0.10, 0.92]
component CDN [0.08, 0.94]

// Dependencies — Customer side
Customer->Need to Acquire Goods
Need to Acquire Goods->Goods and Services
Need to Acquire Goods->Retail Experience
Goods and Services->Physical Store
Goods and Services->E-Commerce Site
Goods and Services->Mobile App
Goods and Services->Telesales
Goods and Services->Social Commerce

// Dependencies — Producer side
Producer->Need to Sell Goods
Need to Sell Goods->Goods and Services
Need to Sell Goods->Inventory and Fulfilment

// Experience layer sits on top of the channels
Retail Experience->Sensory Experience
Retail Experience->Personalisation Engine
Retail Experience->Product Discovery
Retail Experience->Engagement and Loyalty
Retail Experience->Trust and Privacy
Retail Experience->Returns and Reverse Logistics
Retail Experience->Customer Support
Physical Store->Sensory Experience
E-Commerce Site->Virtual / AR Try-On
Mobile App->Virtual / AR Try-On
E-Commerce Site->Personalisation Engine
Mobile App->Personalisation Engine
Social Commerce->Engagement and Loyalty
E-Commerce Site->Product Discovery
Mobile App->Product Discovery
Social Commerce->Product Discovery

// Experience layer draws on behavioural and demographic data
Personalisation Engine->Customer Data Platform
Product Discovery->Customer Data Platform
Engagement and Loyalty->Customer Data Platform
Trust and Privacy->Consent Management
Customer Data Platform->Demographic Segmentation
Customer Data Platform->Societal Behaviour Signals

// Channels depend on commodity infrastructure
Physical Store->Payment Processing
E-Commerce Site->Payment Processing
Mobile App->Payment Processing
Telesales->Payment Processing
Social Commerce->Payment Processing
E-Commerce Site->Identity / KYC
Mobile App->Identity / KYC
Trust and Privacy->Identity / KYC
Returns and Reverse Logistics->Logistics Network
Returns and Reverse Logistics->Inventory and Fulfilment
Customer Support->CRM
Engagement and Loyalty->CRM
E-Commerce Site->Inventory and Fulfilment
Mobile App->Inventory and Fulfilment
Physical Store->Inventory and Fulfilment
Inventory and Fulfilment->Logistics Network

// Digital channels sit on cloud + CDN
E-Commerce Site->Cloud Compute
Mobile App->Cloud Compute
Social Commerce->Cloud Compute
Customer Data Platform->Cloud Compute
E-Commerce Site->CDN
Mobile App->CDN

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast)
evolve Virtual / AR Try-On 0.55
evolve Personalisation Engine 0.70
evolve Social Commerce 0.60
evolve Societal Behaviour Signals 0.50

// Strategic notes
note Differentiation zone — experience and sensing [0.55, 0.22]
note Commodity infrastructure — outsource / utility [0.18, 0.88]
note Trust / consent is hardening under regulation [0.40, 0.55]
